output:
Sunny day in my mind, smiles are all I find, does it show?
Rainy day in my head, smiling voices said, should just let it go.
But in the back of my brain, I feel the emptiness growing again,
a way to visit from my old friend, depression.
Take it easy, you're overreacting, chronic boredom is not a lack of feeling,
prescription drugs won't bring an end.
Oh no, here I go, some hormones up now I'm feeling low,
but I'll try to cry, I'll do my best to keep my spirits high.
